Alba, DP World and Oman’s Nawras: Persian Gulf Equity Preview

-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 
2011-09-22T05:06:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-22/bahrain-s-alba-and-dubai-s-dp-world-persian-gulf-equity-preview.html
Dubai’s  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  gained
the most this month, rising 0.5 percent. Abu Dhabi’s  ADX General
Index (ADSMI)  was little changed. Saudi Arabia’s market is closed for
the weekend.  Aluminium Bahrain BSC (ALBH)  : The company known as Alba
said the price it pays for natural gas will rise to $2.25 for 1
million British thermal units, from $1.50, according to a notice
it received from state-run Bahrain Petroleum Co. The shares were
unchanged at 0.87 dinar.  DP World Ltd. (DPW)  : The Dubai government-controlled
ports operator said Port & Free Zone World FZE has refinanced an
$850 million debt facility secured in part against some of its
shares in DP World. The shares gained 1.9 percent to $9.85.  Omani Qatari Telecommunications Co SAOG (NWRS)  : The
phone company known as Nawras was started with a “neutral”
recommendation at  HSBC Holdings Plc (HSBA)  and a 0.73 rial price
estimate. The shares were unchanged at 0.665 rial.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
